article.headline: Army 64, Yale 48
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Cleveland Richard scored 18 points, 13 in the second half, as Army defeated Yale 64-48 on Saturday for its fourth consecutive victory. Yale (2-5), which turned the ball over on its first three possessions, led only once, 20-19 with 6:35 remaining in the first half. The Black Knights (4-1) then went on a 13-4 run to take a 32-24 halftime lead. Army increased its lead to 37-24 in the first 1:19 of the second half as Richard hit a layup and Julian Simmons a 3-pointer. The Black Knights used a 9-0 run to turn a 46-36 lead with 13:47 left into a 55-36 bulge at the 8:15 mark. Jeremy Hence, who scored 10 points for Army, had a pair of layups during the run. Alex Zampier, who had been averaging 22.3 points for the Bulldogs, struggled to a 4-for-15 shooting day and nine points, tied for the Yale lead with Porter Braswell, Raffi Mantilla and Reggie Willhite.
